@node "Installation"

                                 @{b}Installation@{ub}

-------------------------
 In a dedicated draver
-------------------------

Copy the Rival drawer anywhere on your hard disk and complete system "path" in
the user startup. As example, if Rival drawer has been copied in SYS:Tools,
add in the S:User-Startup file :

   Path SYS:Tools/Rival ADD


-------------------------
 In the operating system
-------------------------

Copy Rival file, Rival.info file and Images drawer in C: and copy all *.catalog
files of the Catalog drawer in SYS:Locale/Catalogs.


                                ----------------


Don't forget to install AMuiDiff tool from StÚphane SARAGAGLIA, available on
Aminet. It is usefull for text files comparison.


@endnode

---------------------------------------\/---------------------------------------

@node "Use"

                                      @{b}Use@{ub}


Rival software is started by clicking the icon or by a command line from shell.

It supports the following settings parameters (tooltypes or shell arguments) :

********************************************************************************
 Description            | Standard key           | Short key    | Default value
                        | (tooltype or arg.)     | (arg. only)  |
********************************************************************************
 Selected directory 1   | INITIAL_DIR_1          | DIR1         | RAM:
 at starting            |                        |              |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Selected directory 2   | INITIAL_DIR_2          | DIR2         | RAM:
 at starting            |                        |              |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Directory differences  | DIR_DIFF_COUNT_MODE    | DCM          | DIR_AND_FILE
 count mode among :     |                        |              |
    DIR_AND_FILE        |                        |              |
    FILE_ONLY           |                        |              |
********************************************************************************

After program starting, a user interface appears on the Ambient screen :

-------------------
 Action bars
-------------------

   Three buttons bars at the top of the main window allow to select action
      - Left bar is for actions relative to first directory tree (left one)
      - Right bar is for actions relative to second directory tree (right one)
      - Center bar is for global actions

-------------------
 Directories trees
-------------------

   Two directory display trees, at left and right position in the main window,
   display compared directory contents informations.

   The layout to display each compared directory (left one and right one) owns :
      - A directory selection popup button to select a new directory to compare
      - A string field with the currently selected directory name
      - An history list popup button to select a previouly compared directory
      - A list tree to display the directory contents

-------------------
 Differences list
-------------------

   A list at the center position in the main window shows the difference for
   each entry.

   Differences count for two directories is based on the directories contents.
   It may be configured according two count principles :

      DIR_AND_FILE directory differences count is
         +1 for a missing directory
         +1 for a missing file
         +1 for two files which are different

      FILE_ONLY directory differences count is
         +1 for a missing file
         +1 for two files which are different

   Differences status for two compared files is based upon the files binary or
   text contents. Comparison never takes into account the compared files external
   attributes like :
      - status flags (ex: reading, writing or deleting protection),
      - last modification date,
      - file linked comments.

-------------------
 Action result
-------------------

   An action status bar displays the last action result at the bottom of the
   main window.

@endnode

